## Additional Information
Note that this change will also require updating the `pom.xml` file to use the Jakarta EE 9 API dependencies instead of the Java EE dependencies. Specifically, the `javax.enterprise` dependencies should be replaced with `jakarta.enterprise` dependencies.

For example, if the `pom.xml` file contains the following dependency:
```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>javax.enterprise</groupId>
    <artifactId>cdi-api</artifactId>
    <version>2.0</version>
</dependency>
```
It should be updated to:
```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>jakarta.enterprise</groupId>
    <artifactId>cdi-api</artifactId>
    <version>4.0</version>
</dependency>
```
Similarly, other dependencies that use the `javax` namespace should be updated to use the `jakarta` namespace.
